   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>“In Memory Of Colonel Charles Young”</head>





<l>Along the shore the tall, thin grass</l>
<l>That fringes that dark river,</l>
<l>While sinuously soft feet pass,</l>
<l>Begins to bleed and quiver.</l>

<l>The great dark voice breaks with a sob</l>
<l>Across the womb of night;</l>
<l>Above your grave the tom-toms throb,</l>
<l>And the hills are weird with light.</l>

<l>The great dark heart is like a well</l>
<l>Drained bitter by the sky,</l>
<l>And all the honeyed lies they tell</l>
<l>Come there to thirst and die.</l>

<l>No lie is strong enough to kill</l>
<l>The roots that work below;</l>
<l>From your rich dust and slaughtered will</l>
<l>A tree with tongues will grow.</l>


            <byline>Countée Cullen</byline>
